<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Narthecium</i> <i>californicum</i> and/or <i>Triantha</i> <i>occidentalis</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Carex</i> <i>luzulina</i>, <i>Darlingtonia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Helenium</i> <i>bigelovii</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>ensifolius</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>nevadensis</i>, <i>Parnassia</i> <i>californica</i> and <i>Rhynchospora</i> <i>alba</i>. Emergent shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Alnus</i> <i>incana</i>. Mosses may be abundant, including <i>Philonotis</i> <i>fontana</i> and <i>Sphagnum</i> <i>teres</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is continuous. </div>
</div>

        
