<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fluvial processes rather than fire primarily disturb stands. However, fires occur in fens during the late part of the growing season in dry years. Fire damage to perennial liliaceous species likely depends upon the depth of the peat layer and whether the belowground biomass burns or whether the fire only consumes above-ground biomass, whereby the plants can sprout from rhizomes.</div>
